BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-AD-truck-leaning-board.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]* [@ image( "21-AD-truck-leaning-board2.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*


A truck carries a slender cylindrical rod with a mass [`m_{rod}=[$m]\:kg`], and length [`l_{rod}=[$l]\:m`].
A block is initially used to keep the rod in place at an angle of [`{\theta}_0=[$tinit]\:^{\circ}`]. The block eventually falls off the truck, and
the rod begins to slip until it reaches its final position at [`{\theta}=[$t]\:^{\circ}`] shown. If the truck is moving at the same
constant acceleration of [`a_{truck}=[$ag]\:m/s^2`], find the minimum coefficient of static friction [`{\mu}_s`] between the rod and the
truck at point [`B`], assuming the vertical wall of the truck is perfectly slippery.

Furthermore, find the angular acceleration [`{\alpha}_{rod}`] of the rod the moment the block loses contact with the rod.


[`{\mu}_s = `][_____]{"$mu"}

[`{\alpha}_{rod} = `][_____]{"$alpha"} [` \boldsymbol{\hat{k}} `] [`rad/s^2`]


END_PGML

